data.description:
Inviting 3 bed, 3.5 bath two-story home in the esteemed Landmark Subdivision, poised on over half an acre and ready for your personal touch. 

Features a finished basement, expansive deck, and generous front and back yards. This residence beckons with potential for your unique style. 

The main level greets you with a bright living area, flowing effortlessly into the dining and kitchen spaces, opening onto a deck perfect for gatherings. It also includes a convenient half bath, spacious coat closet, adjacent to the large heated 2-car garage. Additionally, you’ll find an ample master suite with a full bath and walk-in closet. 

 Upstairs, discover a versatile loft, two sun-filled bedrooms, and a large bathroom. The basement presents a blank canvas, complete with a laundry area, storage closet, full bath, and two additional rooms adaptable for offices, guest spaces, or creative endeavors. 

 The outdoor space is a haven for leisure, featuring a deck, a cozy hot tub area, fire pit, and a serene pond. Set in a scenic neighborhood adorned with parks and sidewalks, this home is a perfect canvas for crafting your ideal Montana lifestyle.

Conveniently located, this home is just a short 13-minute drive to Bozeman International Airport, 20 minutes to Bozeman and Montana State University, 40 minutes to Bridger Bowl Ski area, an hour's scenic drive to world-class skiing in Big Sky, MT, and just under two hours away from countless opportunities to visit Yellowstone National Park or enjoy miles of snowmobile tracks in West Yellowstone. It's also within easy reach of four rivers, endless opportunities for fly fishing, hunting, hiking, kayaking, outdoor climbing, XC skiing and soaking in a multitude of hot springs. 

For those interested in an additional dwelling unit (ADU), the property's covenants permit this, offering a potential avenue for additional stream of income. Please refer to the covenants for more details.
